            <!---->

            <div class="description__text description__text--rich">





                <section class="show-more-less-html" data-max-lines="5">
                    <div class="show-more-less-html__markup show-more-less-html__markup--clamp-after-5
            relative overflow-hidden">
                        <strong>OBJECTIVES<br><br></strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>As an Amanotes’ data engineer you will be leveraging on hundreds terabytes of data from
                                over 3+ billion users to create real business values through practical data
                                solutions<br><br></li>
                        </ul><strong>What You Will Do<br><br></strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Build the Foundation: Design, develop, and maintain robust, scalable ETL/ELT pipelines
                                and modern Data Lake/Warehouse architectures.</li>
                            <li>Drive Automation: Streamline and automate data workflows to improve data reliability and
                                operational efficiency.</li>
                            <li>Prepare for the Future: Modernize and scale our data infrastructure to support advanced
                                AI and machine learning initiatives.</li>
                            <li>Deliver Data Products: Collaborate closely with stakeholders and cross-functional teams
                                to build impactful data-driven solutions, such as anomaly detection systems and A/B test
                                analyzers.<br><br></li>
                        </ul><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>3-4+ years hands-on experience deploying production quality code</li>
                            <li>Core Stack: Strong proficiency in Python, SQL, Apache Airflow, and dbt.</li>
                            <li>Data Warehousing: Deep understanding of analytical Data Warehouses, with a strong
                                preference for Google BigQuery.</li>
                            <li>Data Architecture: Solid grasp of data modeling methodologies (e.g., Kimball, Inmon).
                            </li>
                            <li>Cloud &amp; Infra: Hands-on experience with major cloud platforms (GCP, AWS, or Azure)
                                and comfort navigating Linux environments and Git.</li>
                            <li>Reporting: Experience integrating with and preparing data for BI and visualization
                                tools.<br><br></li>
                        </ul><strong>NICE TO HAVE<br><br></strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Real-Time Data: Experience with streaming ETL processes and tools (Kafka, Apache Spark,
                                Google Pub/Sub).</li>
                            <li>DevOps/DataOps: Experience building CI/CD pipelines for data processes (GitLab, GitHub,
                                Bitbucket).</li>
                            <li>Ecosystem Knowledge: A broad understanding of the modern data and artificial
                                intelligence landscapes.</li>
                            <li>Business Acumen: A strong business mindset with the ability to connect technical data
                                solutions to company goals.</li>
                            <li>Extended Tech: Experience with alternative orchestration tools (Dagster, Prefect) or
                                frontend frameworks (JavaScript/ReactJS) for internal tooling.<br><br></li>
                        </ul><strong>Benefits<br><br></strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>At Amanotes, you will be enjoying the dynamic working environment with unique music
                                culture many benefits as below:</li>
                            <li>Competitive salary upon experience</li>
                            <li>13th month salary</li>
                            <li>Flexible working time. </li>
                            <li>Personal learning and well-being budget</li>
                            <li>Team-building budget</li>
                            <li>Lunch and parking allowance</li>
                            <li>Various learning activities, including internal training &amp; sharing, international
                                conferences, and e-learning (Udemy, Linkedin Learning...).</li>
                            <li>Engaging music events: Music Night, Amasing Night, Music schools…</li>
                            <li>Employee Assistance Program to support mental health &amp; well-being. </li>
                            <li>Minimum 12 days of paid annual leave, plus 10 days of paid sick leave.</li>
                            <li>12 days working from home per year.<br><br></li>
                        </ul><strong>Consent Notice for Personal Data Processing<br><br></strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li> By applying to any position at Amanotes, you acknowledge and agree that your personal
                                data will be collected and processed for recruitment-related purposes. Please read the “
                                Consent Notice for Personal Data Processing ” carefully before submitting your
                                application.</li>
                            <li> Thank you for your interest in joining Amanotes.<br><br></li>
                        </ul><strong>About Amanotes<br><br></strong>We are Amanotes – a dynamic music game company
                        that’s using cutting-edge technology to transform how people experience
